	abstract = {With the emergence of a new variant of coronavirus in 2019, it became important to devote a significant amount of time to reading and identifying relevant studies to better understand COVID-19. It is urgent to sort out important, effective, and meaningful information from large databases to guide scientific research and promote the proper con-trol, prevention, diagnosis, and treatment of COVID-19. Thus, this paper presents an experimental study that shows the application of topic modeling, and data visualization for COVID-19 research from 2010 to 2021 for the All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS), New Delhi, India. The results unveil the focus of scientific research, thereby giving deep in-sights into how the Indian medical society contributes to combating the COVID-19 pandemic.},
